/* =============================================================================
   CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) - STYLESHEET FILE
   =============================================================================
   CSS is what makes websites look good! It controls:
   - Colors, fonts, spacing
   - Layout (how elements are arranged)
   - Animations and transitions
   - Responsive design (how it looks on different screen sizes)
   
   KEY CONCEPTS FOR BEGINNERS:
   - SELECTORS: Target HTML elements to style (e.g., 'nav', '.lesson-card')
   - PROPERTIES: What to change (e.g., 'color', 'background', 'margin')
   - VALUES: The actual values (e.g., 'red', '10px', 'bold')
   - CASCADE: Multiple styles can apply to one element - later ones win!
   - SPECIFICITY: More specific selectors override general ones
   ============================================================================= */

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 1: CSS CUSTOM PROPERTIES (CSS VARIABLES)
   =============================================================================
   CSS Variables (also called "Custom Properties") are like reusable values.
   They start with -- and can be used throughout the file.
   
   Benefits:
   - Easy to change colors across entire site
   - Consistent theming
   - Dark mode support (just change the values)
   
   Here we define our color palette:
   - ivory: Off-white background
   - white: Pure white
   - black: Near-black for text
   - charcoal: Dark gray
   - beige: Warm light gray
   - dark-red: For errors/alerts
   - dark-green: For success states
   ============================================================================= */
:root {
    --ivory: #FFFFF0;
    --white: #FFFFFF;
    --black: #0A0A0A;
    --charcoal: #2A2A2A;
    --beige: #F5F5DC;
    --dark-red: #8B0000;
    --dark-green: #006400;
    --nav-color: #FFFFFF;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 2: ACCESSIBILITY STYLES
   =============================================================================
   These styles help users navigate using keyboards instead of mice.
   
   .skip-link: Hidden by default (positioned off-screen), appears when tabbed to
   This is critical for screen reader users and keyboard-only navigation.
   ============================================================================= */
.skip-link {
    position: absolute;
    top: -40px;
    left: 0;
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 8px 16px;
    z-index: 10000;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
}

.skip-link:focus {
    top: 0;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 3: FOCUS STATES
   =============================================================================
   :focus-visible shows a visible outline when using keyboard navigation.
   This is better than :focus alone because mouse users don't see it.
   The outline helps users know which element is currently selected.
   ============================================================================= */
*:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--nav-color);
    outline-offset: 2px;
}

a:focus-visible,
button:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--nav-color);
    outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 4: GLOBAL RESET
   =============================================================================
   The universal selector (*) targets ALL elements.
   RESET: Removes default browser margins/padding that vary between browsers.
   box-sizing: border-box makes width/height include padding and borders
   (instead of adding them on top), which makes layout calculations easier.
   ============================================================================= */
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 5: BASE TYPOGRAPHY
   =============================================================================
   Base styles for the entire page:
   - font-family: Which font to use (with fallbacks)
   - background-color: Page background
   - color: Default text color
   - line-height: Space between lines (1.6 = 160% of font size)
   ============================================================================= */
body {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    background-color: var(--ivory);
    color: var(--black);
    line-height: 1.6;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 6: HEADING STYLES
   =============================================================================
   All heading tags (h1-h6) get the same styling:
   - Monospace font (like code)
   - Bold weight
   - Uppercase transformation
   - Slight letter spacing adjustment
   ============================================================================= */
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
}

/* Code-related elements also use monospace */
code, pre, .terminal {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 7: NAVIGATION BAR
   =============================================================================
   The fixed header that stays at the top of the page:
   
   position: fixed - Stays in place when scrolling
   top/left/right: 0 - Sticks to all edges
   z-index: 1000 - Ensures it stays above other content
   display: flex - Enables flexbox layout
   justify-content: space-between - Pushes title and links to opposite ends
   align-items: center - Vertically centers content
   ============================================================================= */
nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 16px 32px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    z-index: 1000;
    border-bottom: 4px solid var(--white);
}

.nav-title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
}

.nav-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 32px;
}

.nav-links a {
    color: var(--white);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    position: relative;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 8: NAVIGATION HOVER EFFECTS
   =============================================================================
   ::after creates a pseudo-element (invisible by default)
   On hover, it becomes visible and expands as an underline animation.
   
   transition: Makes the animation smooth over 0.2 seconds
   width: 0 → width: 100% creates the growing line effect
   ============================================================================= */
.nav-links a::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -4px;
    left: 0;
    width: 0;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--white);
    transition: width 0.2s;
}

.nav-links a:hover::after {
    width: 100%;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 9: PROGRESS BAR (FOR FUTURE USE)
   =============================================================================
   A fixed bar below navigation that could show page load progress
   or user progress through a course.
   ============================================================================= */
.progress-container {
    position: fixed;
    top: 60px;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--charcoal);
    z-index: 999;
}

.progress-bar {
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--black);
    width: 0%;
    transition: width 0.3s;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 10: HERO SECTION
   =============================================================================
   The main banner area with the headline and manifesto.
   
   padding: 120px top accounts for the fixed nav bar
   max-width: 1200px - Prevents it from getting too wide on large screens
   margin: 0 auto - Centers it horizontally
   border-bottom: Creates visual separation from next section
   ============================================================================= */
.hero {
    padding: 120px 32px 64px;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border-bottom: 4px solid var(--black);
    background: var(--ivory);
    color: var(--black);
}

.hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--black);
}

.hero .tagline {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    color: var(--charcoal);
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 11: MANIFESTO BOX
   =============================================================================
   A highlighted box containing the site's core message.
   
   background: white - Contrasts with page background
   border: 3px solid black - Thick border for emphasis
   box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 black - Creates "brutalist" offset shadow effect
   ============================================================================= */
.manifesto {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--black);
    color: var(--black);
}

.manifesto p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--black);
}

.manifesto strong {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--black);
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 12: CALL-TO-ACTION BUTTON
   =============================================================================
   Buttons that stand out and encourage clicking.
   
   display: inline-block - Allows margin/padding but doesn't fill container
   transition: all 0.1s - Animates all property changes smoothly
   transform: translate(-4px, -4px) - Moves button up-left on hover
   box-shadow expansion gives "lifting" effect
   ============================================================================= */
.cta-button {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 16px 32px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.1s;
}

.cta-button:hover {
    background: var(--white);
    color: var(--black);
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--black);
    transform: translate(-4px, -4px);
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 13: LESSONS/guides SECTION
   =============================================================================
   Container for tutorial cards.
   
   max-width: 1400px - Slightly wider for more cards
   margin: 0 auto - Centers the section
   ============================================================================= */
.lessons-section {
    padding: 64px 32px;
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

.section-header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
}

.section-header h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.section-header p {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--charcoal);
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 14: CSS GRID FOR LESSON CARDS
   =============================================================================
   display: grid - Enables CSS Grid layout!
   
   grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr))
   This is powerful! It means:
   - Create as many columns as will fit
   - Each column must be at least 320px wide
   - If there's leftover space, distribute it equally (1fr)
   
   This creates a RESPONSIVE layout automatically!
   ============================================================================= */
.lessons-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 24px;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 15: LESSON CARD STYLING
   =============================================================================
   Each tutorial card is a clickable box:
   
   position: relative - Allows positioning child elements absolutely
   cursor: pointer - Shows hand cursor on hover
   transition: all 0.1s - Smooth hover animation
   ============================================================================= */
.lesson-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    padding: 24px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.1s;
    position: relative;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--black);
}

.lesson-card:link,
.lesson-card:visited {
    color: var(--black);
}

.lesson-card:hover {
    background: var(--nav-color);
    color: var(--black);
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--black);
    transform: translate(-4px, -4px);
}

.lesson-card:hover .lesson-number,
.lesson-card:hover .lesson-title,
.lesson-card:hover .lesson-desc {
    color: var(--black);
}

.lesson-card:hover .badge {
    background: var(--white);
    color: var(--black);
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 16: COMPLETED LESSON INDICATOR
   =============================================================================
   When a user completes a lesson, we add the 'completed' class.
   This changes the border color and adds a checkmark.
   
   ::after creates the checkmark content
   position: absolute places it in the corner
   ============================================================================= */
.lesson-card.completed {
    border-color: var(--dark-green);
}

.lesson-card.completed::after {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    top: 16px;
    right: 16px;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--dark-green);
    font-weight: bold;
}

.lesson-card h3 {
    color: var(--black);
}

.lesson-number {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.lesson-title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--black);
}

.lesson-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 17: BADGES (DIFFICULTY LEVELS)
   =============================================================================
   Small tags showing beginner/intermediate/advanced.
   Different styling for different levels.
   ============================================================================= */
.badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    text-transform: uppercase;
}

.badge-beginner {
    background: var(--ivory);
}

.badge-intermediate {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
}

.badge-advanced {
    background: var(--white);
    color: var(--black);
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 18: MODAL (POPUP) STYLES
   =============================================================================
   Modal overlay covers the entire screen:
   - display: none (hidden by default)
   - position: fixed with top/left/right/bottom: 0 (fullscreen)
   - background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8) - Semi-transparent black
   - z-index: 2000 - Above everything else
   
   .active class makes it visible (display: block or flex)
   ============================================================================= */
.modal-overlay {
    display: none;
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
    z-index: 2000;
    overflow-y: auto;
}

.modal-overlay.active {
    display: block;
}

/* =============================================================================
   LESSON MODAL STYLES (for pages using lesson-modal class)
   ============================================================================= */
.lesson-modal {
    display: none;
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
    z-index: 2000;
    overflow-y: auto;
}

.lesson-modal.active {
    display: block;
}

.lesson-modal > .lesson-header {
    background: var(--nav-color);
    color: var(--black);
    padding: 24px 32px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 40px auto 0;
    border: 4px solid var(--black);
    border-bottom: none;
}

.lesson-modal > .lesson-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
}

.lesson-modal .lesson-content {
    background: var(--ivory);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
    border: 4px solid var(--black);
    box-shadow: 12px 12px 0 var(--black);
}

.lesson-modal .lesson-body {
    padding: 32px;
}

.modal {
    background: var(--ivory);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 40px auto;
    border: 4px solid var(--black);
    box-shadow: 12px 12px 0 var(--black);
    padding: 0;
}

.modal-header {
    background: var(--nav-color);
    color: var(--black);
    padding: 24px 32px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
}

.modal-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
}

.close-btn {
    background: var(--white);
    color: var(--black);
    border: 2px solid var(--white);
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}

.close-btn:hover {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
}

.modal-content {
    padding: 32px;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 19: LESSON CONTENT STYLING
   =============================================================================
   Styles for the actual tutorial content within modals:
   - Headings with bottom borders
   - Proper spacing for paragraphs and lists
    ============================================================================= */
.lesson-content {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    padding: 0 32px;
}

.lesson-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 32px 0 16px;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--black);
}

.lesson-content p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.lesson-content ul, .lesson-content ol {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-left: 24px;
}

.lesson-content li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.lesson-content pre {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--ivory);
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    white-space: pre;
}

.lesson-content pre .prompt {
    color: #2ECC71;
}

.lesson-content pre .command {
    color: var(--ivory);
}

.lesson-content pre .output {
    color: #3498DB;
}

.lesson-content pre .comment {
    color: #aaaaaa;
}

.lesson-content pre .variable {
    color: #9cdcfe;
}

.lesson-content pre .keyword {
    color: #569cd6;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 20: TERMINAL/CODE BLOCK STYLING
   =============================================================================
   Dark background for terminal output and code examples.
   Different colors for prompts, commands, and output help readability.
   
   overflow-x: auto - Horizontal scroll if code is too wide
   ============================================================================= */
.terminal-block {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--ivory);
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    white-space: pre;
}

.terminal-block .prompt {
    color: #2ECC71;
}

.terminal-block .command {
    color: var(--white);
}

.terminal-block .output {
    color: var(--beige);
}

.terminal-block .comment {
    color: #aaaaaa !important;
}

.config-block {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--ivory);
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
}

.code-block {
    background: #1e1e1e;
    color: var(--ivory);
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    white-space: pre;
}

.code-block .keyword { color: #569cd6; }
.code-block .function { color: #dcdcaa; }
.code-block .string { color: #ce9178; }
.code-block .number { color: #b5cea8; }
.code-block .comment { color: #6a9955; }
.code-block .variable { color: #9cdcfe; }
.code-block .operator { color: #d4d4d4; }

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 21: HIGHLIGHT BOX
   =============================================================================
   A box to highlight important information or tips.
   Uses a left border for visual emphasis.
   ============================================================================= */
.highlight-box {
    background: var(--beige);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--black);
    padding: 16px;
    margin: 16px 0;
    font-style: italic;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 22: QUIZ SECTION STYLING
   =============================================================================
   Interactive quiz components:
   - Question containers
   - Input fields with focus states
   - Correct/incorrect feedback styling
   - Score display
   ============================================================================= */
.quiz-section {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    padding: 32px;
    margin-top: 32px;
}

.quiz-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    padding-bottom: 16px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--black);
}

.quiz-question {
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    padding-bottom: 24px;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--charcoal);
}

.quiz-question:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
}

.question-text {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.question-text .blank {
    display: inline-block;
    min-width: 120px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--black);
    text-align: center;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--charcoal);
}

.quiz-input {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 300px;
    padding: 12px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    background: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.quiz-input:focus {
    outline: none;
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--black);
}

.quiz-input.correct {
    border-color: var(--dark-green);
    background: #f0fff0;
}

.quiz-input.incorrect {
    border-color: var(--dark-red);
    background: #fff0f0;
}

.quiz-feedback {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 8px;
    display: none;
}

.quiz-feedback.correct {
    color: var(--dark-green);
    display: block;
}

.quiz-feedback.incorrect {
    color: var(--dark-red);
    display: block;
}

.quiz-hint {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-top: 8px;
    display: none;
}

.quiz-hint.visible {
    display: block;
}

.quiz-answer {
    display: none;
    margin-top: 16px;
    padding: 16px;
    background: var(--beige);
    border: 2px solid var(--nav-color);
    font-weight: bold;
}

.quiz-answer.visible {
    display: block;
}

.quiz-options {
    margin: 16px 0;
}

.quiz-options label {
    display: block;
    padding: 8px 12px;
    margin: 8px 0;
    background: var(--white);
    border: 2px solid var(--charcoal);
    cursor: pointer;
}

.quiz-options label:hover {
    border-color: var(--nav-color);
    background: var(--beige);
}

.quiz-submit {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 12px 24px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-right: 12px;
}

.quiz-submit:hover {
    background: var(--white);
    color: var(--black);
}

.quiz-score {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 16px;
    background: var(--beige);
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    display: none;
}

.quiz-score.visible {
    display: block;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 23: ABOUT AND RESOURCES SECTIONS
   =============================================================================
   Styling for informational sections:
   - About section with white background
   - Resources grid for tool links
   ============================================================================= */
.about-section {
    padding: 64px 32px;
    background: var(--white);
    border-top: 4px solid var(--black);
    border-bottom: 4px solid var(--black);
}

.about-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

.about-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
}

.about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
}

.resources-section {
    padding: 64px 32px;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

.resources-section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
}

.resources-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 24px;
}

.resource-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    padding: 24px;
}

.resource-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.resource-card a {
    color: var(--black);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 24: FOOTER STYLING
   =============================================================================
   Dark footer with centered content.
   The copyleft symbol (reversed C) represents the philosophy
   that free software should remain free.
   ============================================================================= */
footer {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 48px 32px;
    text-align: center;
}

footer p {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

footer .copyleft {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 25: RESPONSIVE DESIGN (MEDIA QUERIES)
   =============================================================================
   Media queries change styles based on screen size.
   This is how we make sites work on phones and tablets!
   
   @media (max-width: 768px) means:
   "When the screen is 768px OR SMALLER, apply these styles"
   
   Common breakpoints:
   - 768px: Tablets
   - 480px: Mobile phones
   ============================================================================= */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    nav {
        padding: 12px 16px;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 12px;
    }

    .nav-links {
        gap: 16px;
    }

    .hero {
        padding: 100px 16px 48px;
    }

    .manifesto {
        padding: 20px;
    }

    .lessons-section {
        padding: 48px 16px;
    }

    .modal {
        margin: 20px;
    }

    .modal-content {
        padding: 20px;
    }

    .quiz-section {
        padding: 20px;
    }
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 26: ANIMATIONS (KEYFRAMES)
   =============================================================================
   @keyframes define an animation sequence.
   fadeIn makes elements gradually appear:
   - Start: opacity 0, translated down 20px
   - End: opacity 1, at normal position
   
   This creates a nice entrance effect for lesson cards.
   ============================================================================= */
@keyframes fadeIn {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}

.lesson-card {
    animation: fadeIn 0.4s ease-out;
    animation-fill-mode: both;
}

/* animation-delay: Stagger the cards for a cascading effect */
.lesson-card:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.05s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.1s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.15s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.25s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(6) { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(7) { animation-delay: 0.35s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(8) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(9) { animation-delay: 0.45s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(10) { animation-delay: 0.5s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(11) { animation-delay: 0.55s; }
.lesson-card:nth-child(12) { animation-delay: 0.6s; }

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 27: AUTH MODAL STYLING
   =============================================================================
   The login/register popup modal:
   - display: flex when active (for centering)
   - Dark semi-transparent background
   - White box with thick border
   ============================================================================= */
.auth-modal {
    display: none;
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
    z-index: 2000;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
}

.auth-modal.active {
    display: flex;
}

.auth-box {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 4px solid var(--black);
    padding: 32px;
    max-width: 400px;
    width: 90%;
    position: relative;
    box-shadow: 12px 12px 0 var(--black);
}

.close-auth {
    position: absolute;
    top: 8px;
    right: 12px;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    font-size: 2rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--black);
}

.close-auth:hover {
    color: var(--charcoal);
}

.auth-tabs {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
}

.auth-tab {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    padding: 8px 24px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--black);
}

.auth-tab.active {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
}

.auth-form {
    display: none;
}

.auth-form.active {
    display: block;
}

.form-group {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.form-group label {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.form-group input {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 12px;
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    background: var(--white);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
}

.form-group input:focus {
    outline: none;
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--black);
}

/* Error and success messages */
.auth-error {
    color: var(--dark-red);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: none;
}

.auth-error.show {
    display: block;
}

.auth-success {
    color: var(--dark-green);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    display: none;
}

.auth-success.show {
    display: block;
}

/* User avatar and logout button */
.user-avatar {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
}

.logout-btn {
    background: none;
    border: none;
    color: var(--white);
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: none;
}

.logout-btn:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
}

/* =============================================================================
   BLOCK 28: PROJECTS SECTION
   =============================================================================
   Larger cards for project tutorials.
   minmax(400px, 1fr) - Projects need more width than lessons.
   ============================================================================= */
.projects-section {
    padding: 64px 32px;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
}

.projects-section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.section-subtitle {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
}

.projects-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(400px, 1fr));
    gap: 24px;
}

@media (max-width: 500px) {
    .projects-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
}

.project-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 3px solid var(--black);
    padding: 32px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--black);
    transition: all 0.1s;
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--black);
}

.project-card:hover {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    transform: translate(-4px, -4px);
    box-shadow: 12px 12px 0 var(--black);
}

.project-card:hover .project-icon,
.project-card:hover h3,
.project-card:hover p,
.project-card:hover .project-level {
    color: var(--white);
}

.project-card:hover .project-level {
    border-color: var(--white);
}

.project-card:hover .stack-item {
    background: var(--white);
    color: var(--black);
}

.project-icon {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.project-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.project-card p {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

.project-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.stack-item {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--black);
}

.project-level {
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--black);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    display: inline-block;
}
